write/src/cli/requirements.rs` is also stubbed with `NotYetImplemented` errors for all subcommands:\n- `requirements draft --idea <idea>`\n- `requirements quick --idea <idea>`\n- `requirements show <run_id>`\n- `requirements answer <run_id>`\n\n### 3. agent_execution Context - Core Agent Integration\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `model.rs` (167 lines) - Data models for invocations\n- `service.rs` (339 lines) - Service layer with BackendResolver\n- `session.rs` (127 lines) - Session reuse logic\n\n**Critical Coupling Point - StageContract:**\n- `InvocationRequest` (lines 70-82) contains `StageContract`\n- `AgentExecutionService::invoke()` (lines 159-255) directly evaluates the contract after invocation:\n  ```rust\n  request.stage_contract.evaluate_permissive(&parsed_payload)\n    .map_err(|error| map_contract_error(error, &request))?;\n  ```\n- The contract evaluation is **tightly coupled** - the service directly calls `StageContract::evaluate_permissive()` to validate outputs\n\n**Key Models:**\n- `CancellationToken` - Atomic flag with async notification for cancellation\n- `InvocationRequest` - Complete invocation specification including stage_contract, role, backend target, payload, timeout\n- `InvocationEnvelope` - Complete response with parsed payload, metadata, timestamp\n- `BackendResolver` - Cascading resolution: workspace defaults → project config → explicit override\n- `CapabilityCheck` - Backend capability validation structure\n\n**Session Management:**\n- `SessionMetadata` - Per-role, per-backend session tracking\n- `PersistedSessions` - Vec of sessions loaded/saved via `SessionStorePort`\n- Session reuse allowed only for: Implementer, Reviewer, QaValidator roles\n- OpenRouter backend does NOT support session reuse\n\n### 4. workflow_composition Context - Contract Registry & Validation\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `contracts.rs` (255 lines) - **THE STAGE CONTRACT REGISTRY**\n- `engine.rs` (2292 lines) - Execution engine (very large)\n- `payloads.rs` (131 lines) - Typed stage payload models\n- `retry_policy.rs` - Retry/terminal semantics\n- `renderers.rs` - Markdown artifact generation\n\n**Stage Contract Registry (`contracts.rs`):**\n\nThree contract families:\n- **Planning**: prompt_review, planning, docs_plan, ci_plan → `PlanningPayload`\n- **Execution**: implementation, plan_and_implement, apply_fixes, docs_update, ci_update → `ExecutionPayload`\n- **Validation**: qa, docs_validation, ci_validation, acceptance_qa, review, final_review, completion_panel → `ValidationPayload`\n\n**StageContract Implementation:**\n```rust\npub struct StageContract {\n    pub stage_id: StageId,\n    pub family: ContractFamily,\n}\n```\n\n**Evaluation Pipeline (line 116-144):**\n1. Schema validation (JSON → typed payload via serde)\n2. Semantic validation (domain rules)\n3. Rendering (Markdown artifact)\n4. Optional outcome check (only if non-permissive mode)\n\n**Tight Coupling Evidence:**\n- `evaluate()` → calls `evaluate_permissive()` → calls `validate_schema()` → calls `validate_semantics()` → calls `render()`\n- Each validation step is a private method tightly bound to the contract\n- Error mapping happens in agent_execution service (lines 331-337)\n\n**Payload Models:**\n- `PlanningPayload`: problem_framing, assumptions, proposed_work[], readiness\n- `ExecutionPayload`: change_summary, steps[], validation_evidence[], outstanding_risks[]\n- `ValidationPayload`: outcome (enum), evidence[], findings_or_gaps[], follow_up_or_amendments[]\n- `ReviewOutcome` enum: Approved, ConditionallyApproved, RequestChanges, Rejected\n\n### 5. Adapters - Filesystem & Test Backend\n\n**fs.rs (870 lines)** - Comprehensive filesystem adapter:\n- `FileSystem` - Basic I/O utilities with atomic writes using temp files + rename\n- `FsProjectStore` - Read/create projects, list project IDs\n- `FsJournalStore` - Append-only NDJSON journal\n- `FsArtifactStore` - List payloads and artifacts\n- `FsRuntimeLogStore` - NDJSON runtime logs (reads only latest file)\n- `FsRunSnapshotStore` - Read run.json with semantic validation\n- `FsActiveProjectStore` - Track active project\n- `FsRawOutputStore` - Persist backend raw output\n- `FsSessionStore` - Session persistence\n- `FsPayloadArtifactWriteStore` - Atomic pair write with staging\n- `FsAmendmentQueueStore` - Amendment queue persistence\n- `FsRuntimeLogWriteStore` - Append runtime logs\n\n**Directory Layout** (PROJECT_SUBDIRS constant, lines 34-42):\n```\nproject_root/\n├── history/payloads/\n├── history/artifacts/\n├── runtime/logs/\n├── runtime/backend/\n├── runtime/temp/\n├── amendments/\n├── rollback/\n├── project.toml\n├── prompt.md\n├── run.json\n├── journal.ndjson\n└── sessions.json\n```\n\n**stub_backend.rs (319 lines)** - Test double for AgentExecutionPort:\n- Configurable delay, availability, unsupported stages\n- Transient failure simulation (fail N times then succeed)\n- Stage payload overrides (sequences of values)\n- Cancellation tracking\n- Deterministic canned payloads per stage\n- Token count simulation (word counting)\n\n### 6. CLI Structure - Command Handlers\n\n**requirements.rs (41 lines)** - STUB:\n- Four subcommands (draft, quick, show, answer) - ALL NOT YET IMPLEMENTED\n- Uses `AppError::NotYetImplemented` sentinel\n\n**Other CLI commands:**\n- `run.rs` (388 lines) - Full run execution handler\n- `config.rs`, `init.rs`, `daemon.rs`, `flow.rs`, `project.rs`, `conformance.rs` - Other commands\n\n### 7. Shared Error Types\n\n**error.rs (163 lines):**\n\n**AppError enum** - 30+ variants covering:\n- Workspace lifecycle: AlreadyInitialized, WorkspaceConflict, UnsupportedWorkspaceVersion\n- Project lifecycle: ProjectNotFound, DuplicateProject, ActiveRunDelete\n- Configuration: UnknownConfigKey, InvalidConfigValue\n- Execution: RunStartFailed, ResumeFailed, UnsupportedFlow, PreflightFailed\n- Backend integration: BackendUnavailable, CapabilityMismatch, InvocationFailed, InvocationTimeout, InvocationCancelled\n- Validation: RemediationExhausted, CompletionBlocked\n- Data integrity: CorruptRecord, JournalSequence, AmendmentQueueError\n\n**ContractError enum** - 4 variants mapping to FailureClass:\n- `SchemaValidation` → `SchemaValidationFailure`\n- `DomainValidation` / `RenderError` → `DomainValidationFailure`\n- `QaReviewOutcome` → `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n**FailureClass enum** - 6 categories for retry semantics:\n- TransportFailure, SchemaValidationFailure, DomainValidationFailure, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailure\n\n### 8. Shared Domain Types\n\n**Key types:**\n- `BackendFamily` enum: Claude, Codex, OpenRouter, Stub\n- `BackendRole` enum: Planner, Implementer, Reviewer, QaValidator, CompletionJudge\n- `StageId` enum: 16 stage variants (prompt_review through ci_validation)\n- `FlowPreset` enum: Standard, QuickDev, DocsChange, CiImprovement\n- `SessionPolicy` enum: NewSession, ReuseIfAllowed\n- `FailureClass` enum: 6 failure categories\n- `StageCursor`: (stage, cycle, attempt, completion_round)\n- `ResolvedBackendTarget`: (backend, model) pair\n- `CapabilityMetadata`: supports_structured_output, supports_session_reuse, supports_cancellation, supported_stages[]\n\n### 9. Test Structure\n\n**Tests directory:**\n```\ntests/\n├── cli.rs                           # Integration/CLI tests\n├── unit.rs                          # Test module harness\n└── unit/\n    ├── active_project_test.rs       # Project selection\n    ├── adapter_contract_test.rs     # Adapter contract validation (38KB!)\n    ├── agent_execution_test.rs      # Agent service tests\n    ├── config_test.rs               # Config parsing\n    ├── domain_test.rs               # Domain type tests\n    ├── flow_preset_test.rs          # Flow preset semantics\n    ├── flow_semantics_test.rs       # Stage plan resolution\n    ├── journal_test.rs              # Journal parsing\n    ├── project_run_record_test.rs   # Run state management\n    ├── query_test.rs                # Queries on run state\n    ├── renderer_test.rs             # Markdown rendering\n    ├── retry_policy_test.rs         # Retry semantics\n    ├── stage_contract_test.rs       # Contract validation (16KB)\n    ├── stub_backend_test.rs         # Stub adapter behavior\n    ├── workflow_engine_test.rs      # Execution engine (96KB! - LARGEST TEST)\n    └── workspace_test.rs            # Workspace initialization\n```\n\n**Test sizes indicate focus areas:**\n- `workflow_engine_test.rs` (96KB) - Most comprehensive test coverage\n- `adapter_contract_test.rs` (38KB) - Adapter port contract validation\n- `stage_contract_test.rs` (16KB) - Contract evaluation tests\n- Full integration CLI test (`cli.rs` - 83KB)\n\n### 10. Cargo.toml Dependencies\n\n```toml\n[dependencies]\nchrono = \"0.4\" (clock, serde)\nclap = \"4.5\" (derive)\nschemars = \"0.8\"\nserde = \"1\" (derive)\nserde_json = \"1\"\nthiserror = \"2\"\ntokio = \"1\" (macros, rt-multi-thread, sync, time)\ntoml = \"0.8\"\ntoml_edit = \"0.22\"\ntracing = \"0.1\"\ntracing-subscriber = \"0.3\" (fmt)\n\n[dev-dependencies]\njsonschema = \"0.18\"\ntempfile = \"3\"\n```\n\nKey architectural choices:\n- **async/await** via Tokio (multi-threaded runtime)\n- **typed errors** via thiserror\n- **schema validation** via schemars/jsonschema\n- **config** via TOML (with atomic writes)\n- **logging** via tracing\n\n### Key Architecture Patterns Observed\n\n1. **Port-Adapter Pattern**: Clear separation of ports (traits) vs adapters (implementations)\n   - `AgentExecutionPort` trait in service.rs\n   - `RawOutputPort`, `SessionStorePort` traits\n   - All adapters in `adapters/` directory\n\n2. **Tight StageContract Coupling**: \n   - `StageContract` lives in `workflow_composition/contracts.rs`\n   - Used directly in `agent_execution/service.rs` for validation\n   - Imported via `use crate::contexts::workflow_composition::contracts::StageContract`\n   - Evaluation happens synchronously after invocation\n\n3. **Cascading Backend Resolution**:\n   ```\n   role.default_target() \n   → workspace_defaults override\n   → project_config override\n   → explicit_model_override\n   ```\n\n4. **Session Reuse Policy**:\n   - Only for Implementer, Reviewer, QaValidator\n   - Requires both role AND backend+model support\n   - Tracked durably in `sessions.json`\n\n5. **Run State as Source of Truth**:\n   - `run.json` (RunSnapshot) canonical state\n   - `journal.ndjson` (append-only events)\n   - Never inferred - always loaded\n   - Semantic validation on load catches inconsistencies\n\n---\n\n**All file paths are absolute as requested:**\n\nKey files for understanding the project:\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/Cargo.toml`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/mod.rs`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/model.rs`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/stub_backend.rs`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/requirements.rs`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs`\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2b8bdaa1ce67534b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75503\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 63220</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"36dfa1de-6185-4dcd-ac73-de5f18bf85fd","uuid":"8f8185af-2032-47d4-af18-0a44f57318ad","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the ralph-burning-rewrite project at /root/new-ralph-burning. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall directory structure (src/, tests/, etc.)\n2. The current module structure in src/contexts/ - especially requirements_drafting/ (which should be stubs)\n3. The agent_execution