{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user provided a comprehensive feature specification for Loop 10 of the ralph-burning-rewrite project: implementing \"Requirements Drafting and Project Seed Handoff\". This is a Rust binary project implementing an orchestrator called `ralph-burning`. The spec requires:\n   - A `RequirementsRun` state model persisted at `.ralph-burning/requirements/<run-id>/run.json`\n   - Four structured contracts: `question_set`, `requirements_draft`, `requirements_review`, `project_seed`\n   - Four CLI commands: `requirements draft`, `requirements quick`, `requirements show`, `requirements answer`\n   - Generalizing `agent_execution` from workflow-only `StageContract` coupling to a domain-neutral interface\n   - Extensive filesystem stores, failure invariants, and test coverage (Gherkin scenarios + unit tests)\n   - The output format must be an implementation notes markdown file with specific H1/H2 headings\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Rust modular monolith with bounded contexts (DDD)\n   - Port-adapter pattern for side effects\n   - Structured stage contracts: schema validation → domain validation → rendering\n   - `StageContract` (workflow) vs new `RequirementsContract` (requirements) - must NOT add requirements stages to `StageId` enum\n   - `InvocationContract` enum generalizing the agent execution interface\n   - NDJSON journal for append-only event sourcing\n   - Atomic filesystem writes with staging directories\n   - Seed pair rollback semantics (if prompt.md fails, remove project.json too)\n   - Answer validation from TOML with required question enforcement\n   - Review outcomes: approved, conditionally_approved (complete with follow-ups), request_changes/rejected (fail run)\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **src/shared/error.rs** (MODIFIED)\n     - Changed 4 invocation error variants from `stage_id: StageId` to `contract_id: String`\n     - Added 3 new error variants for requirements\n     ```rust\n     CapabilityMismatch { backend: String, contract_id: String, details: String },\n     InvocationFailed { backend: String, contract_id: String, failure_class: FailureClass, details: String },\n     InvocationTimeout { backend: String, contract_id: String, timeout_ms: u64 },\n     InvocationCancelled { backend: String, contract_id: String },\n     InvalidRequirementsState { run_id: String, details: String },\n     AnswerValidationFailed { run_id: String, details: String },\n     SeedPersistenceFailed { run_id: String, details: String },\n     ```\n\n   - **src/contexts/agent_execution/model.rs** (MODIFIED)\n     - Added `InvocationContract` enum with `Stage(StageContract)` and `Requirements { label: String }` variants\n     - Changed `InvocationRequest.stage_contract: StageContract` to `InvocationRequest.contract: InvocationContract`\n     - Updated `CapabilityCheck` to use `contract_id: String` and take `&InvocationContract`\n     ```rust\n     #[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n     pub enum InvocationContract {\n         Stage(StageContract),\n         Requirements { label: String },\n     }\n     impl InvocationContract {\n         pub fn label(&self) -> String { ... }\n         pub fn stage_id(&self) -> Option<StageId> { ... }\n         pub fn stage_contract(&self) -> Option<&StageContract> { ... }\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs** (MODIFIED)\n     - `AgentExecutionPort::check_capability` now takes `&InvocationContract` instead of `&StageContract`\n     - `invoke()` only validates stage contracts: `if let Some(stage_contract) = request.contract.stage_contract() { ... }`\n     - All error mapping functions use `request.contract.label()` instead of `request.stage_contract.stage_id`\n\n   - **src/contexts/agent_execution/mod.rs** (MODIFIED)\n     - Added `InvocationContract` to pub use exports\n\n   - **src/adapters/stub_backend.rs** (MODIFIED)\n     - Added `label_payload_overrides` and `label_payload_counters` fields\n     - Added `with_label_payload()` and `with_label_payload_sequence()` methods\n     - `check_capability` takes `&InvocationContract`, requirements always supported\n     - `invoke` uses `request.contract.label()` for errors, `payload_for_contract()` for payload lookup\n     - Added `canned_requirements_payload()` returning deterministic payloads for question_set, requirements_draft, requirements_review, project_seed\n\n   - **src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs** (MODIFIED - 4 edits)\n     - Added `InvocationContract` to imports\n     - Changed `stage_contract: stage_entry.contract` to `contract: InvocationContract::Stage(stage_entry.contract)`\n     - Changed 3 error construction sites from `stage_id,` to `contract_id: stage_id.to_string(),`\n\n   - **src/contexts/requirements_drafting/mod.rs** (MODIFIED)\n     - Added module declarations: `pub mod contracts; pub mod model; pub mod renderers; pub mod service;`\n\n   - **src/contexts/requirements_drafting/model.rs** (CREATED)\n     - `RequirementsRun` state model with all spec-required fields\n     - `RequirementsMode` (Draft, Quick), `RequirementsStatus` (Drafting, AwaitingAnswers, Completed, Failed)\n     - `RequirementsStageId` enum (QuestionSet, RequirementsDraft, RequirementsReview, ProjectSeed)\n     - `RequirementsJournalEvent` and `RequirementsJournalEventType`\n     - `RequirementsReviewOutcome` with `allows_completion()` method\n     - Payload structs: `QuestionSetPayload`, `RequirementsDraftPayload`, `RequirementsReviewPayload`, `ProjectSeedPayload`\n     - `Question` struct with id, prompt, rationale, required flag, suggested_default\n     - `PersistedAnswers` and `AnswerEntry`\n\n   - **src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs** (CREATED)\n     - `RequirementsContract` with `question_set()`, `draft()`, `review()`, `seed()` constructors\n     - `evaluate()` method following schema → domain → render pipeline\n     - `RequirementsValidatedBundle` and `RequirementsPayload` enum\n     - Domain validation: duplicate question IDs, empty required fields, flow preset validation, findings required for non-approval\n     - Note: Uses `StageId::Planning` as placeholder in `ContractError` stage_id field (since ContractError is tied to StageId)\n\n   - **src/contexts/requirements_drafting/renderers.rs** (CREATED)\n     - `render_question_set()`, `render_requirements_draft()`, `render_requirements_review()`, `render_project_seed()`\n     - Deterministic Markdown output from structured payloads\n     - Project seed renderer includes suggested `ralph-burning project create` command\n\n   - **src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs** (CREATED)\n     - `RequirementsStorePort` trait with 15 methods for filesystem operations\n     - `RequirementsService<A, R, S, Q>` generic over agent port, raw output, sessions, requirements store\n     - `draft()`: creates run, generates questions, transitions to awaiting_answers or continues\n     - `quick()`: creates run in quick mode, skips questions, goes straight to draft→review→seed\n     - `show()`: returns `RequirementsShowResult` derived from run.json and journal\n     - `answer()`: validates run state, opens $EDITOR, validates answers, resumes from boundary\n     - `continue_after_answers()`: draft → review (check outcome) → seed generation with rollback\n     - Failure invariants: partial payload/artifact failures don't transition state\n     - Seed rollback: if prompt.md fails after project.json, both removed\n\n   - **Key existing files read for understanding (not modified):**\n     - `src/shared/domain.rs` - StageId (16 variants), FlowPreset, BackendRole, StageCursor, ProjectId, RunId\n     - `src/contexts/workflow_composition/payloads.rs` - PlanningPayload, ExecutionPayload, ValidationPayload, ReviewOutcome\n     - `src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` - StageContract with evaluate/evaluate_permissive pipeline\n     - `src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` - RunSnapshot, JournalEvent patterns\n     - `src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs` - Event serialization, sequence validation\n     - `tests/unit.rs` - 17 test module registrations\n\n4. Errors and Fixes:\n   - Attempted to Write to mod.rs without reading first - got \"File has not been read yet\" error. Fixed by reading first.\n   - Attempted to Edit error.rs without reading first - got same error. Fixed by reading first.\n   - No user feedback/corrections received.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - Extensive deliberation on how to generalize agent_execution without breaking existing code. Considered: trait objects (Clone issue), separate invoke methods, optional stage_contract, parallel error variants. Final decision: `InvocationContract` enum + changing error field types from `StageId` to `String`. This was the cleanest generalization.\n   - Verified test assertions use `matches!(error, AppError::Variant { .. })` pattern (with `..`), so field name/type changes don't break them.\n   - Identified all constructor sites for affected errors: ~7 in service.rs, ~7 in stub_backend.rs, ~2 in engine.rs, 1 in workflow_engine_test.rs.\n\n6. All User Messages:\n   - Message 1: The full feature specification for Loop 10 (Requirements Drafting and Project Seed Handoff) with detailed acceptance criteria, files to modify/create, master prompt context, and system guardrails. Format requires implementation notes markdown output.\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Background agent: Adding FsRequirementsStore to adapters/fs.rs (launched, not yet completed)\n   - Background agent: Updating CLI requirements.rs handler (launched, not yet completed)\n   - Update test files for generalized contract interface:\n     - tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs: line 1574 (`request.stage_contract.stage_id`), line 1619 (`request.stage_contract.stage_i