{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RxKf1BBQKmY6rDqndVCy6s","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→@workspace-init\n     2→Feature: Workspace initialization\n     3→  The CLI initializes a v1 ralph-burning workspace in the current directory.\n     4→\n     5→  @workspace-init-fresh\n     6→  Scenario: init fresh workspace\n     7→    Given the current directory does not contain a \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n     8→    When I run \"ralph-burning init\"\n     9→    Then the file \".ralph-burning/workspace.toml\" should exist\n    10→    And the command should exit successfully\n    11→\n    12→  @workspace-init-existing\n    13→  Scenario: init already-initialized workspace\n    14→    Given the current directory already contains a \".ralph-burning/workspace.toml\" file\n    15→    When I run \"ralph-burning init\"\n    16→    Then the command should fail with a clear already-initialized error\n    17→\n    18→  @workspace-init-layout\n    19→  Scenario: init verifies directory structure\n    20→    Given the current directory does not contain a \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    21→    When I run \"ralph-burning init\"\n    22→    Then the directory \".ralph-burning/projects\" should exist\n    23→    And the directory \".ralph-burning/requirements\" should exist\n    24→    And the directory \".ralph-burning/daemon/tasks\" should exist\n    25→    And the directory \".ralph-burning/daemon/leases\" should exist\n    26→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01D5aQn8eVUbDi6V9Rkr4gBX","session_id":"36dfa1de-6185-4dcd-ac73-de5f18bf85fd","uuid":"d8a2e5db-240d-4062-a588-a37dfafe156b"}
