{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0167MMFr3KB7dkDVT9xS7V3p","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Resume for Docs and CI Presets\n     2→  The `run resume` command reconstructs docs_change and ci_improvement runs\n     3→  from durable stage boundaries using the same shared engine semantics as\n     4→  standard-flow resume.\n     5→\n     6→  # SC-NONSTD-RESUME-001\n     7→  Scenario: Resume a failed docs_change run from docs_update\n     8→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"docs-resume\" using flow \"docs_change\"\n     9→    And project \"docs-resume\" is selected as active\n    10→    And a previous \"run start\" failed after \"docs_plan\" completed and \"docs_update\" exhausted retries\n    11→    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    12→    Then the command exits successfully\n    13→    And the resumed run keeps the original run_id\n    14→    And the docs_plan stage is not re-executed\n    15→    And the first resumed stage is \"docs_update\" with attempt 1\n    16→\n    17→  # SC-NONSTD-RESUME-002\n    18→  Scenario: Resume a failed ci_improvement run from ci_update\n    19→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"ci-resume\" using flow \"ci_improvement\"\n    20→    And project \"ci-resume\" is selected as active\n    21→    And a previous \"run start\" failed after \"ci_plan\" completed and \"ci_update\" exhausted retries\n    22→    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    23→    Then the command exits successfully\n    24→    And the resumed run keeps the original run_id\n    25→    And the ci_plan stage is not re-executed\n    26→    And the first resumed stage is \"ci_update\" with attempt 1\n    27→\n    28→  # SC-NONSTD-RESUME-003\n    29→  Scenario: Resume a paused docs_change snapshot with pending amendments\n    30→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"docs-paused\" using flow \"docs_change\""}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01D5aQn8eVUbDi6V9Rkr4gBX","session_id":"36dfa1de-6185-4dcd-ac73-de5f18bf85fd","uuid":"70d2a683-f975-4ad9-ad00-f2f4c6e0c80f"}
