{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PaXyQz2ihAyjCvhHfcUYoy","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both files are in good shape. Here is a summary of what was done:\n\n---\n\n**Created test file:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/requirements_drafting_test.rs`\n\n**Updated module registration:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit.rs` (appended the `requirements_drafting_test` module)\n\n**Compilation verified:** `cargo check --test unit` passes cleanly with no errors or warnings.\n\nThe test file covers all four requested categories:\n\n1. **Model tests (5 tests):**\n   - `RequirementsRun::new_draft` creates Draft mode, Drafting status\n   - `RequirementsRun::new_quick` creates Quick mode, Drafting status\n   - `RequirementsRun::is_terminal` returns true for Completed/Failed, false for Drafting/AwaitingAnswers\n   - `RequirementsReviewOutcome::allows_completion` returns true for Approved/ConditionallyApproved, false for RequestChanges/Rejected\n   - `RequirementsStageId::as_str` round-trips through serde serialization/deserialization for all four variants\n\n2. **Contract tests (10 tests):**\n   - Valid question set JSON accepted\n   - Duplicate question IDs fail domain validation\n   - Empty question prompt fails domain validation\n   - Valid draft JSON accepted\n   - Empty problem_summary fails domain validation\n   - Empty goals fails domain validation\n   - Valid review JSON accepted\n   - request_changes with empty findings fails domain validation\n   - Valid seed JSON accepted\n   - Empty project_id fails domain validation\n\n3. **Renderer tests (5 tests):**\n   - `render_question_set` produces deterministic Markdown with questions, required markers, rationale, and suggested defaults\n   - `render_question_set` with empty questions produces \"No clarifying questions needed.\"\n   - `render_requirements_draft` produces Markdown with all sections (Problem Summary, Goals, Non-Goals, Constraints, Acceptance Criteria, Risks, Recommended Flow)\n   - `render_requirements_review` produces Markdown with outcome\n   - `render_project_seed` produces Markdown with project details and suggested command\n\n4. **Service integration tests (4 async tests in `service_integration` submodule):**\n   - `quick()` creates a run and completes through the draft-review-seed pipeline\n   - After quick completes, `show()` returns a Completed run with `seed_prompt_path`\n   - `draft()` with default stub (empty questions) continues directly to completion\n   - `draft()` with stub returning questions transitions to AwaitingAnswers"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7567ee52695e2889 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 65122\ntool_uses: 41\nduration_ms: 211525</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"36dfa1de-6185-4dcd-ac73-de5f18bf85fd","uuid":"7c986a5a-4d7d-4293-ab77-eff005ba05e4","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Create a comprehensive unit test file at /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/requirements_drafting_test.rs\n\nAlso add the module registration to /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit.rs by appending:\n```\n#[path = \"unit/requirements_drafting_test.rs\"]\nmod requirements_drafting_test;\n```\n\nThe tests should cover:\n\n1. **Model tests:**\n   - `RequirementsRun::new_draft` creates a run in Draft mode, Drafting status\n   - `RequirementsRun::new_quick` creates a run in Quick mode, Drafting status\n   - `RequirementsRun::is_terminal` returns true for Completed and Failed, false for Drafting/AwaitingAnswers\n   - `RequirementsReviewOutcome::allows_completion` returns true for Approved and ConditionallyApproved, false for RequestChanges and Rejected\n   - `RequirementsStageId::as_str` round-trips\n\n2. **Contract tests:**\n   - `RequirementsContract::question_set().evaluate()` accepts valid question set JSON\n   - Question set with duplicate IDs fails domain validation\n   - Question set with empty question prompt fails domain validation\n   - `RequirementsContract::draft().evaluate()` accepts valid draft JSON\n   - Draft with empty problem_summary fails domain validation\n   - Draft with empty goals fails domain validation\n   - `RequirementsContract::review().evaluate()` accepts valid review JSON\n   - Review with request_changes outcome and empty findings fails domain validation\n   - `RequirementsContract::seed().evaluate()` accepts valid seed JSON\n   - Seed with empty project_id fails domain validation\n\n3. **Renderer tests:**\n   - `render_question_set` produces deterministic Markdown with questions\n   - `render_question_set` with empty questions produces \"No clarifying questions needed.\"\n   - `render_requirements_draft` produces Markdown with all sections\n   - `render_requirements_review` produces Markdown with outcome\n   - `render_project_seed` produces Markdown with project details and suggested command\n\n4. **Service integration tests** (using StubBackendAdapter and FsRequirementsStore):\n   - `quick()` mode creates a run and completes it through draft→review→seed pipeline\n   - After quick completes, `show()` returns a Completed run with seed_prompt_path\n   - `draft()` with stub that returns empty questions continues directly to completion\n   - `draft()` with stub that returns questions transitions to AwaitingAnswers\n\nFor fixtures, use:\n- `tempfile::tempdir()` for temp directories\n- `ralph_burning::contexts::workspace_governance::initialize_workspace` for workspace init (import from workspace_test module's `initialize_workspace_fixture`)\n- `ralph_burning::adapters::stub_backend::StubBackendAdapter`\n- `ralph_burning::adapters::fs::{FsRawOutputStore, FsSessionStore, FsRequirementsStore}`\n- `ralph_burning::contexts::agent_execution::service::AgentExecutionService`\n- `ralph_burning::contexts::requirements_drafting::service::RequirementsService`\n- `chrono::{TimeZone, Utc}` for deterministic timestamps\n\nImportant patterns from the existing codebase:\n- Tests use `#[tokio::test(flavor = \"multi_thread\")]` for async tests\n- The StubBackendAdapter's canned payload for `question_set` returns `{\"questions\": []}` by default (empty), meaning draft mode will fall through to direct completion\n- To test draft mode with questions, use `StubBackendAdapter::default().with_label_payload(\"requirements:question_set\", json!({\"questions\": [{\"id\": \"q1\", \"prompt\": \"Test question?\", \"rationale\": \"Testing\", \"required\": true}]}))` \n- The workspace needs to be initialized before running requirements commands. Use `crate::workspace_test::initialize_workspace_fixture(&temp_dir.path())` to create a workspace fixture.\n- The FsRequirementsStore needs subdirectories under `.ralph-burning/requirements/<run-id>/`. The service handles creation.\n- The service's `draft()` and `quick()` return the run_id string.\n- `RequirementsService::new(agent_service, requirements_store)` constructs the service.\n\nThe test file should have the standard `#![forbid(unsafe_code)]` is NOT needed at the test level (tests don't use it). Just write the tests.\n\nMake sure the test code compiles and follows the patterns in the existing test files. Refer to:\n- tests/unit/stub_backend_test.rs for StubBackendAdapter usage \n- tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs for AgentExecutionService test patterns\n- tests/unit/stage_contract_test.rs for contract validation test patterns\n\nNOTE: The `with_label_payload` method takes `(&str, Value)` args. Check the actual method signature from the stub_backend source:\n```rust\npub fn with_label_payload(mut self, label: &str, payload: Value) -> Self\n```\n","agentId":"a7567ee52695e2889","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both files are in good shape. Here is a summary of what was done:\n\n---\n\n**Created test file:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/requirements_drafting_test.rs`\n\n**Updated module